OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FUK's last opencast mine    
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Faccused of licence breach  
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, The operator of the UK's last opencast 
OL,6, coal mine has been accused of breaching
OL,7, its licence after inspectors found it  
OL,8, was mining outside its permitted area. 
OL,10,FMerthyr Tydfil's Ffos-y-Fran mine      
OL,11,Fproduces two-thirds of the UK's coal   
OL,12,Fand was supposed to close in September 
OL,13,Fas its planning permission had expired.
OL,15,FSince then more than 200,000 tonnes of 
OL,16,Fcoal have been extracted.              
OL,18,FOperator Merthyr (South Wales) Ltd said
OL,19,Fit would not be appropriate to comment 
OL,20,F"while the appeal process is ongoing". 
